Bare Creek Bike Park App Privacy Policy
Last Updated: February 26, 2025
Introduction
Welcome to the Bare Creek Bike Park App ("App"). This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use our App. We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about our practices.
Summary

We do not collect or store your personal data
We use weather data from the Australian Bureau of Meteorology
Our App is open source and hosted on GitHub
The App may be accessed globally but is primarily designed for users in New South Wales, Australia

Information We Do Not Collect
The Bare Creek Bike Park App is designed with privacy in mind. We do not:

Collect or store personal information
Track your location
Use cookies or similar tracking technologies
Create user profiles or accounts
Share any data with third parties for marketing purposes
Store any user preferences or settings on our servers

Information Usage
Weather Data
Our App displays weather data that is obtained directly from the Australian Bureau of Meteorology (BOM). This data is publicly available and is retrieved in real-time when you use the App. We do not store this data beyond what is necessary for the App's immediate functionality.
Technical Information
When you use our App, standard technical information may be processed temporarily on your device. This includes:

The time of access
Weather conditions data displayed
Functional data necessary for the App to operate

This information is not transmitted to us or any third parties and remains solely on your device.
Third-Party Services
The App uses the following third-party services:

Australian Bureau of Meteorology (BOM): We access publicly available weather data from BOM to display current and historical weather conditions relevant to the Bare Creek Bike Park. We do not share any user information with BOM.

Open Source
The Bare Creek Bike Park App is open source software. The source code is available on GitHub, allowing anyone to review how the App works, including its privacy practices.
Children's Privacy
The App does not knowingly collect any information from children under the age of 13.
International Data Transfer
While the App is primarily designed for users in New South Wales, Australia, it may be accessed globally. No user data is collected or transferred internationally.
Your Rights
Since we do not collect personal data, there is no personal information for you to access, correct, or delete. However, if you have any questions or concerns about our privacy practices, please contact us using the information provided below.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date.
Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or the App, please contact us at:

Email: [insert your contact email]
